## Procedures.ObservableProcedureModel.setReturnTypes() method

Sets whether the procedure has a return value (empty array) or no return value (null).

The built-in procedure model does not support procedures that have actual return types (i.e. non-empty arrays, e.g. \['number'\]). If you want your procedure block to have return types, you need to implement your own procedure model.

<b>Signature:</b>

```typescript
setReturnTypes(types: string[] | null): this;
```

|  types | string\[\] \| null |  |
